{"id":14880907,"mediaExerciseId":"b239f356-10e9-4fbd-81d8-876a76318bfe","exerciseName":"9","chapterName":"5","chapterTitle":"Introduction to Valuation:The Time Value of Money","groupId":612293,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":147,"solutions":[{"id":6368771,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will determine how long it will take to save enough money to buy the car based on the given conditions.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The time it takes before we obtain a specific amount of money can be calculated using the formula for the number of periods. This is given by:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Number of Periods}&=\\dfrac{\\ln\\left(\\frac{\\text{Future value}}{\\text{Present value}}\\right)}{\\ln(1+\\text{Rate}}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Since all of the values here are already given in the problem, we can simply substitute those to the formula above.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Number of Periods}&=\\dfrac{\\ln\\left(\\frac{\\$245,000}{\\$50,000}\\right)}{\\ln(1+0.043)}\\\\[15 pt]\n&=37.75\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThis means that based on the given conditions, it will take $37.75$ years before the person can save up enough money to buy the car. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"f3d994db-8719-4cbb-9c02-96f82400ad00","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":